column29:
Senator is located approximately 500 metres south west from The Bank of England, occupying a substantial island site on the south side of Queen Victoria Street with over 150 metres of impressive frontage. This prime location has attracted a diverse range of office occupiers from the banking, corporate, legal, professional and media sectors and boasts a wealth of local amenity.

Senator offers 10 underground stations all within a 10-minute walk. Crossrail will improve accessibility even further with fast cross-London connections, arriving in nearby Moorgate in 2018. Discover the Cycle Superhighway that runs alongside Senator for the easiest cycle access and use the Santander Cycles that are just a 1-minute walk away. Or take in river views on the Thames Clipper from Blackfriars.

column29: Located on the bank of the River Thames, 58 Victoria Embankment’s stunning traditional frontage creates a memorable first impression and a distinct sense of arrival. The new Grade A accommodation provides innovative office space, set to resonate with today’s modern occupiers. The building serves as a hub for discerning businesses with shared meeting room space, shared event space, a coffee shop, lounge and bar area for all tenants and a communal roof terrace. The building is a short walk from the new Blackfriars station which serves the Thameslink, District & Circle line.

column29:
18 St Swithin's Lane is located in the heart of the City and benefits from excellent transport links. The building is located immediately opposite Cannon Street Station, serviced by the District & Circle underground lines and mainline rail network. Bank Station is only 100 metres away with additional links to the Northern, Central, Waterloo & City, Circle, District and DLR lines.

The building is also a short walk away from extensive amenities the City Core has to offer.
